SQL stands for Structured Query Language. It is a standard language used for accessing and
manipulating databases. Most of the actions you need to perform on a batabase are done with SQL
Above is an example of a simple SQL statement to display all customer information in the Customers
table with a name of Mary. Notice that it ends with a semicolon (;).
- SQL is NOT case sensitive: select is the same as SELECT
- Database systems require semicolon (;) after each SQL statement. So two SQL statement can
be written in one line as long as you separate them with with a semicolon.
